"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.13.10\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.13.10</span> Platform</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">כִּיּוֹר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kiyor)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:13\">2CH 6:13</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מִגְדָּל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(migdal)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:4\">NEH 8:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">βῆμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(bēma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc13:26\">2MA 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd9:42\">1ES 9:42</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/PTZ-0072_platform_ruins.jpg\" alt=\"Ruins of a platform\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Ruins of a platform (© Ray Pritz by United Bible Societies)</figcaption></figure>The platform was a large raised surface on which someone stood to address a crowd of people. The one described in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:13\">2CH 6:13</a> was made of bronze, and was 2.5 meters (8 feet) square and 1.5 meters (5 feet) high. These dimensions may serve as an approximate model for all of the references above, although the others may have been made of stone (as in the illustration) or wood.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Many cultures are familiar with a special place or structure from which a person addresses an assembled crowd.</p>\n<p>The Hebrew word <em>migdal</em> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:4\">NEH 8:4</a> literally means “tower.” <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> “pulpit” sounds anachronistic, even though the structure upon which Ezra stood fulfilled a purpose similar to that of a modern pulpit in some Christian traditions. <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr> “dais” is accurate but obscure for most English speakers. “Platform” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr>) or “high platform” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr>) is good. The same rendering should be used at <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd9:42\">1ES 9:42</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
